'“Perhaps,” I said.',
'Chapter VIII',
'Pan Dan Chee and I lost all sense of time, so long were we in the pits of Horz without food or water.',
'It could not have been more than two days, as we still had strength; and more than two days without water will sap the strength of the best of men.',
'Twice more we saw the light and heard the laughter.',
'That laugh!',
'I can hear it yet.',
'I tried to think that it was human.',
'I didn’t want to go mad.',
'Pan Dan Chee said, “Let’s find it and drink its blood!”',
'“No, Pan Dan Chee,” I counseled.',
'“We are men, not beasts.”',
'“You are right,” he said.',
'“I was losing control.”',
'“Let’s use our heads,” I said.',
'“He knows always where we are, because always he can see the light of our torch.',
