'“You don’t mean to say that you eat ulsio!”',
'“A great delicacy,” said the creature.',
'“Have you nothing else?” demanded Pan Dan Chee.',
'“There is a little of Ro Tan Bim left,” said the THING, “but he is getting a bit high even for an epicure like me.”',
'Pan Dan Chee looked at me.',
'“I am not hungry,” I said “Come!',
'Let’s try to get out of here.”',
'I turned to the old man.',
'“Which corridor leads out into the city?” I asked.',
'“You must rest,” he said; “then I will show you.',
'Lie down upon that couch and rest.”',
'I had always heard that it is best to humor the insane; and as I was asking a favor of this creature, it seemed the wise thing to do.',
'Furthermore, both Pan Dan Chee and I were very tired; so we lay down on the couch and the old man drew up a bench and sat down beside us.',
'He commenced to talk in a low, soothing voice.',
'“You are very tired,” he said, over and over again monotonously, his great eyes fixed first upon one of us and then upon the other.',
'I felt my muscles relaxing.',
'I saw Pan Dan Chee’s lids drooping.',
'“Soon you will be asleep,” whispered the old man of the pits.',
'“You will sleep and sleep and sleep, perhaps for ages as have these others.',
'You will only awaken when I tell you to or when I die—and I shall never die.',
'You robbed Hor Kai Lan of his harness and weapons.”',
'He looked at me as he spoke.',
'“Hor Kai Lan would be very angry were he to awaken and find that you have stolen his weapons, but Hor Kai Lan will not awaken.',
